23namespace
24{
25
26template <typename T>
27using Remapping = std::unordered_map<const T *, const T *>;
28
29class Rewriter : public TIntermRebuild
30{
31 private:
32 const std::set<ImmutableString> &mKeywords;
33 IdGen &mIdGen;
34 Remapping<TField> modifiedFields;
35 Remapping<TFieldList> mFieldLists;
36 Remapping<TFunction> mFunctions;
37 Remapping<TInterfaceBlock> mInterfaceBlocks;
38 Remapping<TStructure> mStructures;
39 Remapping<TVariable> mVariables;
40 std::map<ImmutableString, std::string> mPredefinedNames;
41 std::string mNewNameBuffer;
42
43 private:
44 template <typename T>
45 ImmutableString maybeCreateNewName(T const &object)
46 {
47 if (needsRenaming(object, false))
48 {
49 auto it = mPredefinedNames.find(Name(object).rawName());
50 if (it != mPredefinedNames.end())
51 {
52 return ImmutableString(it->second);
53 }
54 return mIdGen.createNewName(Name(object)).rawName();
55 }
56 return Name(object).rawName();
57 }
58
59 const TField *createRenamed(const TField &field)
60 {
61 auto *renamed =
62 new TField(const_cast<TType *>(&getRenamedOrOriginal(*field.type())),
63 maybeCreateNewName(field), field.line(), field.symbolType());
64
65 return renamed;
66 }
67
68 const TFieldList *createRenamed(const TFieldList &fieldList)
69 {
70 auto *renamed = new TFieldList();
71 for (const TField *field : fieldList)
72 {
73 renamed->push_back(const_cast<TField *>(&getRenamedOrOriginal(*field)));
74 }
75 return renamed;
76 }
77
78 const TFunction *createRenamed(const TFunction &function)
79 {
80 auto *renamed =
81 new TFunction(&mSymbolTable, maybeCreateNewName(function), function.symbolType(),
82 &getRenamedOrOriginal(function.getReturnType()),
83 function.isKnownToNotHaveSideEffects());
84
85 const size_t paramCount = function.getParamCount();
86 for (size_t i = 0; i < paramCount; ++i)
87 {
88 const TVariable &param = *function.getParam(i);
89 renamed->addParameter(&getRenamedOrOriginal(param));
90 }
91
92 if (function.isDefined())
93 {
94 renamed->setDefined();
95 }
96
97 if (function.hasPrototypeDeclaration())
98 {
99 renamed->setHasPrototypeDeclaration();
100 }
101
102 return renamed;
103 }
104
105 const TInterfaceBlock *createRenamed(const TInterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock)
106 {
107 TLayoutQualifier layoutQualifier = TLayoutQualifier::Create();
108 layoutQualifier.blockStorage = interfaceBlock.blockStorage();
109 layoutQualifier.binding = interfaceBlock.blockBinding();
110
111 auto *renamed =
112 new TInterfaceBlock(&mSymbolTable, maybeCreateNewName(interfaceBlock),
113 &getRenamedOrOriginal(interfaceBlock.fields()), layoutQualifier,
114 interfaceBlock.symbolType(), interfaceBlock.extension());
115
116 return renamed;
117 }
118
119 const TStructure *createRenamed(const TStructure &structure)
120 {
121 auto *renamed =
122 new TStructure(&mSymbolTable, maybeCreateNewName(structure),
123 &getRenamedOrOriginal(structure.fields()), structure.symbolType());
124
125 renamed->setAtGlobalScope(structure.atGlobalScope());
126
127 return renamed;
128 }
129
130 const TType *createRenamed(const TType &type)
131 {
132 TType *renamed;
133
134 if (const TStructure *structure = type.getStruct())
135 {
136 renamed = new TType(&getRenamedOrOriginal(*structure), type.isStructSpecifier());
137 renamed->setQualifier(type.getQualifier());
138 }
139 else if (const TInterfaceBlock *interfaceBlock = type.getInterfaceBlock())
140 {
141 renamed = new TType(&getRenamedOrOriginal(*interfaceBlock), type.getQualifier(),
142 type.getLayoutQualifier());
143 }
144 else
145 {
146 LOGIC_ERROR(); // Can't rename built-in types.
147 renamed = nullptr;
148 }
149
150 if (type.isArray())
151 {
152 renamed->makeArrays(type.getArraySizes());
153 }
154 renamed->setPrecise(type.isPrecise());
155 renamed->setInvariant(type.isInvariant());
156 renamed->setMemoryQualifier(type.getMemoryQualifier());
157 renamed->setLayoutQualifier(type.getLayoutQualifier());
158
159 return renamed;
160 }
161
162 const TVariable *createRenamed(const TVariable &variable)
163 {
164 auto *renamed = new TVariable(&mSymbolTable, maybeCreateNewName(variable),
165 &getRenamedOrOriginal(variable.getType()),
166 variable.symbolType(), variable.extension());
167
168 return renamed;
169 }
170
171 template <typename T>
172 const T *tryGetRenamedImpl(const T &object, Remapping<T> *remapping)
173 {
174 if (!needsRenaming(object, true))
175 {
176 return nullptr;
177 }
178
179 if (remapping)
180 {
181 auto it = remapping->find(&object);
182 if (it != remapping->end())
183 {
184 return it->second;
185 }
186 }
187
188 const T *renamedObject = createRenamed(object);
189
190 if (remapping)
191 {
192 (*remapping)[&object] = renamedObject;
193 }
194
195 return renamedObject;
196 }
197
198 const TField *tryGetRenamed(const TField &field)
199 {
200 return tryGetRenamedImpl(field, &modifiedFields);
201 }
202
203 const TFieldList *tryGetRenamed(const TFieldList &fieldList)
204 {
205 return tryGetRenamedImpl(fieldList, &mFieldLists);
206 }
207
208 const TFunction *tryGetRenamed(const TFunction &func)
209 {
210 return tryGetRenamedImpl(func, &mFunctions);
211 }
212
213 const TInterfaceBlock *tryGetRenamed(const TInterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock)
214 {
215 return tryGetRenamedImpl(interfaceBlock, &mInterfaceBlocks);
216 }
217
218 const TStructure *tryGetRenamed(const TStructure &structure)
219 {
220 return tryGetRenamedImpl(structure, &mStructures);
221 }
222
223 const TType *tryGetRenamed(const TType &type)
224 {
225 return tryGetRenamedImpl(type, static_cast<Remapping<TType> *>(nullptr));
226 }
227
228 const TVariable *tryGetRenamed(const TVariable &variable)
229 {
230 return tryGetRenamedImpl(variable, &mVariables);
231 }
232
233 template <typename T>
234 const T &getRenamedOrOriginal(const T &object)
235 {
236 const T *renamed = tryGetRenamed(object);
237 if (renamed)
238 {
239 return *renamed;
240 }
241 return object;
242 }
243
244 template <typename T>
245 bool needsRenamingImpl(const T &object) const
246 {
247 const SymbolType symbolType = object.symbolType();
248 switch (symbolType)
249 {
250 case SymbolType::BuiltIn:
251 case SymbolType::AngleInternal:
252 case SymbolType::Empty:
253 return false;
254
255 case SymbolType::UserDefined:
256 break;
257 }
258
259 const ImmutableString name = Name(object).rawName();
260 if (mKeywords.find(name) != mKeywords.end())
261 {
262 return true;
263 }
264
265 if (name.beginsWith(kAngleInternalPrefix))
266 {
267 return true;
268 }
269
270 return false;
271 }
272
273 bool needsRenaming(const TField &field, bool recursive) const
274 {
275 return needsRenamingImpl(field) || (recursive && needsRenaming(*field.type(), true));
276 }
277
278 bool needsRenaming(const TFieldList &fieldList, bool recursive) const
279 {
280 ASSERT(recursive);
281 for (const TField *field : fieldList)
282 {
283 if (needsRenaming(*field, true))
284 {
285 return true;
286 }
287 }
288 return false;
289 }
290
291 bool needsRenaming(const TFunction &function, bool recursive) const
292 {
293 if (needsRenamingImpl(function))
294 {
295 return true;
296 }
297
298 if (!recursive)
299 {
300 return false;
301 }
302
303 const size_t paramCount = function.getParamCount();
304 for (size_t i = 0; i < paramCount; ++i)
305 {
306 const TVariable &param = *function.getParam(i);
307 if (needsRenaming(param, true))
308 {
309 return true;
310 }
311 }
312
313 return false;
314 }
315
316 bool needsRenaming(const TInterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock, bool recursive) const
317 {
318 return needsRenamingImpl(interfaceBlock) ||
319 (recursive && needsRenaming(interfaceBlock.fields(), true));
320 }
321
322 bool needsRenaming(const TStructure &structure, bool recursive) const
323 {
324 return needsRenamingImpl(structure) ||
325 (recursive && needsRenaming(structure.fields(), true));
326 }
327
328 bool needsRenaming(const TType &type, bool recursive) const
329 {
330 if (const TStructure *structure = type.getStruct())
331 {
332 return needsRenaming(*structure, recursive);
333 }
334 else if (const TInterfaceBlock *interfaceBlock = type.getInterfaceBlock())
335 {
336 return needsRenaming(*interfaceBlock, recursive);
337 }
338 else
339 {
340 return false;
341 }
342 }
343
344 bool needsRenaming(const TVariable &variable, bool recursive) const
345 {
346 return needsRenamingImpl(variable) ||
347 (recursive && needsRenaming(variable.getType(), true));
348 }
349
350 public:
351 Rewriter(TCompiler &compiler, IdGen &idGen, const std::set<ImmutableString> &keywords)
352 : TIntermRebuild(compiler, false, true), mKeywords(keywords), mIdGen(idGen)
353 {}
354
355 PostResult visitSymbolPost(TIntermSymbol &symbolNode)
356 {
357 const TVariable &var = symbolNode.variable();
358 if (needsRenaming(var, true))
359 {
360 const TVariable &rVar = getRenamedOrOriginal(var);
361 return *new TIntermSymbol(&rVar);
362 }
363 return symbolNode;
364 }
365
366 PostResult visitFunctionPrototype(TIntermFunctionPrototype &funcProtoNode)
367 {
368 const TFunction &func = *funcProtoNode.getFunction();
369 if (needsRenaming(func, true))
370 {
371 const TFunction &rFunc = getRenamedOrOriginal(func);
372 return *new TIntermFunctionPrototype(&rFunc);
373 }
374 return funcProtoNode;
375 }
376
377 PostResult visitDeclarationPost(TIntermDeclaration &declNode) override
378 {
379 Declaration decl = ViewDeclaration(declNode);
380 const TVariable &var = decl.symbol.variable();
381 if (needsRenaming(var, true))
382 {
383 const TVariable &rVar = getRenamedOrOriginal(var);
384 return *new TIntermDeclaration(&rVar, decl.initExpr);
385 }
386 return declNode;
387 }
388
389 PostResult visitFunctionDefinitionPost(TIntermFunctionDefinition &funcDefNode) override
390 {
391 TIntermFunctionPrototype &funcProtoNode = *funcDefNode.getFunctionPrototype();
392 const TFunction &func = *funcProtoNode.getFunction();
393 if (needsRenaming(func, true))
394 {
395 const TFunction &rFunc = getRenamedOrOriginal(func);
396 auto *rFuncProtoNode = new TIntermFunctionPrototype(&rFunc);
397 return *new TIntermFunctionDefinition(rFuncProtoNode, funcDefNode.getBody());
398 }
399 return funcDefNode;
400 }
401
402 PostResult visitAggregatePost(TIntermAggregate &aggregateNode) override
403 {
404 if (aggregateNode.isConstructor())
405 {
406 const TType &type = aggregateNode.getType();
407 if (needsRenaming(type, true))
408 {
409 const TType &rType = getRenamedOrOriginal(type);
410 return TIntermAggregate::CreateConstructor(rType, aggregateNode.getSequence());
411 }
412 }
413 else
414 {
415 const TFunction &func = *aggregateNode.getFunction();
416 if (needsRenaming(func, true))
417 {
418 const TFunction &rFunc = getRenamedOrOriginal(func);
419 switch (aggregateNode.getOp())
420 {
421 case TOperator::EOpCallFunctionInAST:
422 return TIntermAggregate::CreateFunctionCall(rFunc,
423 aggregateNode.getSequence());
424
425 case TOperator::EOpCallInternalRawFunction:
426 return TIntermAggregate::CreateRawFunctionCall(rFunc,
427 aggregateNode.getSequence());
428
429 default:
430 return TIntermAggregate::CreateBuiltInFunctionCall(
431 rFunc, aggregateNode.getSequence());
432 }
433 }
434 }
435 return aggregateNode;
436 }
437
438 const void predefineName(const ImmutableString name, std::string prePopulatedName)
439 {
440 mPredefinedNames[name] = prePopulatedName;
441 }
442};
443
444} // anonymous namespace
445
446////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
447
448bool sh::RewriteKeywords(TCompiler &compiler,
449 TIntermBlock &root,
450 IdGen &idGen,
451 const std::set<ImmutableString> &keywords)
452{
453 Rewriter rewriter(compiler, idGen, keywords);
454 const auto &inputAttrs = compiler.getAttributes();
455 for(const auto & var : inputAttrs)
456 {
457 rewriter.predefineName(ImmutableString(var.name), var.mappedName);
458 }
459 if (!rewriter.rebuildRoot(root))
460 {
461 return false;
462 }
463 return true;
464}
